PydanticAI
PydanticAI is a Python agent framework designed to facilitate the development of production-grade applications utilizing Generative AI.

Agents
Agents are one of the core concepts in PydanticAI, representing components that assist in building applications.

Common Tools
Common Tools are features within PydanticAI that provide essential functionalities for application development.

Dependencies
Dependencies in PydanticAI refer to the required elements that enable the framework's components to work together.

Messages and chat history
Messages and chat history is a feature in PydanticAI that focuses on managing communication within applications.

Multi-agent Applications
Multi-agent Applications refers to applications that utilize multiple agents working collaboratively.

Function Tools
Function Tools are various tools included in PydanticAI to enhance its functionalities.

Model Providers
Model Providers represent various sources of AI models integrated into PydanticAI.

Anthropic
Anthropic is a specific provider of AI models that can be utilized within PydanticAI.

Bedrock
Bedrock is another model provider integrated into the PydanticAI framework.

Cohere
Cohere offers AI models that can be used within PydanticAI for different applications.

Gemini
Gemini provides additional AI models for integration in PydanticAI applications.

Google
Google's models are accessible and can be utilized within the PydanticAI framework.

Groq
Groq is also a model provider featured in PydanticAI.

Mistral
Mistral represents yet another AI model provider integrated within PydanticAI.

OpenAI
OpenAI is a prominent model provider included in the PydanticAI framework.

Graphs
Graphs in PydanticAI refer to the feature related to representation and manipulation of data structures.

Evals
Evals refers to the evaluation components within PydanticAI for testing functionality.

MCP
Model Context Protocol (MCP) is a structured approach within PydanticAI for managing context in conversations.

Client
The Client refers to the component in PydanticAI that interacts with users or other systems.

MCP Run Python
MCP Run Python is a feature for executing Python scripts within the MCP framework.

Server
The Server is part of the infrastructure necessary for hosting the PydanticAI framework.

Command Line Interface (CLI)
The Command Line Interface (CLI) in PydanticAI provides a way to interact with the framework through commands.

Debugging and Monitoring
Debugging and Monitoring tools are features in PydanticAI that help in maintaining application stability.

Unit Testing
Unit Testing features in PydanticAI are designed to ensure the reliability of the code.

Examples
Examples in PydanticAI provide use cases and templates for developers working with the framework.

Bank Support
Bank Support represents a specific example providing guidance on integrating banking functionalities with PydanticAI.

Chat App with FastAPI
The Chat App with FastAPI is an example application demonstrating how to use PydanticAI with FastAPI.

Flight Booking
Flight Booking is an illustrative example of functionalities that can be built using PydanticAI.

Pydantic Model
The Pydantic Model is an exemplary representation of how to structure data within PydanticAI.

Question Graph
The Question Graph example shows how to manage data structures related to querying within PydanticAI.

RAG
RAG stands for Retrieval-Augmented Generation, a functionality that can be implemented through PydanticAI.

SQL Generation
SQL Generation refers to capabilities in PydanticAI for automating database query creation.

Stream Markdown
Stream Markdown is an example illustrating how to process and display Markdown content using PydanticAI.

Stream Whales
Stream Whales serves as an example of real-time data processing within PydanticAI.

Weather Agent
Weather Agent is an illustrative application that obtains and processes weather data using PydanticAI.
